    "Each 350/330 fluorescence ratio trace is first smoothed via a Savitzky-Golay filter (window length 21, polynomial order two) and fitted with the two-state thermal denaturation model:",
    "where α N, β N and α D, β D are the intercept and slope of the linear baselines of the native (N) and denatured (D) states, respectively, R is the gas constant, ΔH D-N is the enthalpy of equilibrium between the native and the denatured state, and T M is the apparent melting temperature.",
